cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on understanding how people make decisions around sharing content on social media, which involves aspects of social influence, human-computer interaction, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to support sharing and information diffusion, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The study also involves a user study and open-ended responses, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the proposed process model of sharing, which could be relevant to cs.SOC (Social and Community Computing).
